          "type": "text",
          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The stored procedure "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "usp_Lookup_GetAccountListForTariffReport_Updated",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is designed to retrieve a list of accounts associated with a specific tariff report. It logs the usage of the report and then queries the database to return account details filtered by agency code and tariff class. The procedure is part of the "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Report",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " schema and interacts with several tables in the "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Billing",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " schema, as well as a user-defined function and another stored procedure for logging purposes."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "2. Complexity Level: Medium"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The complexity level of this stored procedure is considered medium. It involves multiple table joins, a user-defined function, and a call to another stored procedure for logging. The use of a split function to handle a comma-separated list adds to the complexity, as does the need to manage transaction isolation levels."
        }
